                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.6176 F 51/219: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-08-19T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 19, 1926—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>25. For Bussell<note n="47" xml:id="d347fn47">C. T. Bussell, assistant to the
                        General Receiver of Customs of Liberia.</note> from Castle. Since sending my
                    No. 24, August 11, 1 p.m.<note n="48" xml:id="d347fn48">Not printed.</note> the
                    Department has talked with Firestone who says <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“They will not accept Planting Agreement as passed by Legislature, but
                            that Harvey Firestone, Junior, is sailing immediately for Liberia in the
                            hope that satisfactory adjustments can be made and that if this is
                            accomplished they can lay out a program for Liberia which will be
                            helpful and progressive.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
